HEADWORD: Demisemiquaver
<hw>Dem`i*sem"i*qua`ver</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<fld>(Mus.)</fld> <def>A short note, equal in time to the half of a
semiquaver, or the thirty-second part of a whole note.</def>⟦br⟧
